mpoa.name: mpoa
mpoa.contactinfo: Technical Support Avaya Communications, Inc. Telephone from US: 800-237-0016 Telephone from North America: 1-800-242-2121
mpoa.description: The MIB module to implement RFC1483,MPOA/AAL5 protocol

MpoaOperValue.name: MpoaOperValue
MpoaOperValue.description: Represents the operational status of the vsp or link. The value of initial is used when the VSP/link was administratively enabled but the configuration is incorrect, and the VSP/ link cannot be activated.

MpoaResourceId.name: MpoaResourceId
MpoaResourceId.description: Represents the resource id of either an MPOA link or PVC. Before creating a link or PVC, a valid resource id is obtained via GETs for variables in the mpoaResourceMgmtGroup. The resource id is one of the indicies in the mpoaAtmLinkTable and the mpoaPvcTable.

mpoaNextLinkResourceId.name: mpoaNextLinkResourceId
mpoaNextLinkResourceId.description: This variable contains the next available Resource Id to be used when creating a link. Before creating a link, a GET of this variable must be requested. This value should be used in the mpoaAtmLinkIndex variable.

mpoaNextPvcResourceId.name: mpoaNextPvcResourceId
mpoaNextPvcResourceId.description: This variable contains the next available Resource Id to be used when creating a PVC. Before creating a PVC, a GET of this variable must be requested. This value should be used in mpoaPvcResIndex variable.

mpoaVirtualSwitchPortTable.name: mpoaVirtualSwitchPortTable
mpoaVirtualSwitchPortTable.description: A table of all the VSPs created for aal5 traffic on the atm module. The maximum number of expected entries is 128.

mpoaVirtualSwitchPortEntry.name: mpoaVirtualSwitchPortEntry
mpoaVirtualSwitchPortEntry.description: An entry containing management information pertaining to an mpoa VSP.

mpoaVspIndex.name: mpoaVspIndex
mpoaVspIndex.description: The VSP Id number in the range of 1 to 128.

mpoaVspAdminStatus.name: mpoaVspAdminStatus
mpoaVspAdminStatus.description: This variable is used to administratively enable or disable the VSP. This variable must not be included with any other variables in a SET. To modify or delete the VSP, the admin state must first be changed to disable. Then a second PDU must be sent to handle the modify or delete.

mpoaVspOperStatus.name: mpoaVspOperStatus
mpoaVspOperStatus.description: This variable gives the operational status of the vsp. The value of initial is used when the VSP was administratively enabled but the configuration is incorrect, and the VSP cannot be activated.

mpoaVspName.name: mpoaVspName
mpoaVspName.description: A unique 31-character ascii string used to name the VSP.

mpoaVspEncapsulationType.name: mpoaVspEncapsulationType
mpoaVspEncapsulationType.description: The type of packets used on this VSP.

mpoaVspPktReplication.name: mpoaVspPktReplication
mpoaVspPktReplication.description: This value can only be configured at the time of VSP creation. Packet replication simulates multi- casting by sending a single packet to a default VC that copies the packet to multiple PVCs. Choose yes only if there are multiple ATM links, with more than 1 remote destination.

mpoaVspLoadShare.name: mpoaVspLoadShare
mpoaVspLoadShare.description: This value should be yes if load-sharing is desired between PVCs. If load-sharing is desired, then both default PVCs should be configured for this VSP.

mpoaVspDefaultPort.name: mpoaVspDefaultPort
mpoaVspDefaultPort.description: This variable contains the preferred default port. In case of fail-over or load-sharing, this port is the primary port.

mpoaVspDefaultVc_port1.name: mpoaVspDefaultVc_port1
mpoaVspDefaultVc_port1.description: This variable is only applicable for non-replicating ports and should be ignored for replicating ports. This variable contains the pvc resource id of the primary default VC if the default physical port is port 1. It contains the pvc resource id of the secondary default VC if load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen and the default physical port is port 2. A secondary default VC must be configured if either load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen. The default VC is used to send packets with unknown unicast and broadcast destination MAC addresses.

mpoaVspDefaultVc_port2.name: mpoaVspDefaultVc_port2
mpoaVspDefaultVc_port2.description: This variable is only applicable for non-replicating ports and should be ignored for replicating ports. This variable contains the pvc resource id of the primary default VC if the default physical port is port 2. It contains the pvc resource id of the secondary default VC if load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen and the default physical port is port 1. A secondary default VC must be configured if either load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen.

mpoaVspMulticastChan_port1.name: mpoaVspMulticastChan_port1
mpoaVspMulticastChan_port1.description: This variable is only applicable for replicating ports and should be ignored for non-replicating ports. This variable contains the channel id of the primary default multicast channel if the default physical port is port 1. It contains the channel id of the secondary multicast channel if load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen and the default physical port is port 2.

mpoaVspMulticastChan_port2.name: mpoaVspMulticastChan_port2
mpoaVspMulticastChan_port2.description: This variable is only applicable for replicating ports and should be ignored for non-replicating ports. This variable contains the channel id of the primary default multicast channel if the default physical port is port 2. It contains the channel id of the secondary multicast channel if load-sharing or fail-over has been chosen and the default physical port is port 1.

mpoaVspRowStatus.name: mpoaVspRowStatus
mpoaVspRowStatus.description: This variable is included with every SET PDU to indicate whether the SET PDU contains a create or delete transaction type.

mpoaAtmLinkTable.name: mpoaAtmLinkTable
mpoaAtmLinkTable.description: A table of all the ATM links created for MPOA traffic on the ATM module. The maximum number of expected entries is 16k.

mpoaAtmLinkEntry.name: mpoaAtmLinkEntry
mpoaAtmLinkEntry.description: An entry containing management information pertaining to an mpoa ATM Link. This table is doubly- indexed by the VSP id (index) and the link id (index).

mpoaAtmLinkVspIndex.name: mpoaAtmLinkVspIndex
mpoaAtmLinkVspIndex.description: Index of the VSP that this link is associated with.

mpoaAtmLinkIndex.name: mpoaAtmLinkIndex
mpoaAtmLinkIndex.description: The ATM link id number. This variable comprises the second index in the link row entry. To get a valid link index, application must first get value of mpoaNextLinkResourceId, before creating a new entry.

mpoaAtmLinkAdminStatus.name: mpoaAtmLinkAdminStatus
mpoaAtmLinkAdminStatus.description: This variable is used to administratively enable or disable the link. This variable must not be included with any other variables in a SET. To modify or delete the link, the admin state must first be changed to disable. Then a second PDU must be sent to handle the modify or delete.

mpoaAtmLinkOperStatus.name: mpoaAtmLinkOperStatus
mpoaAtmLinkOperStatus.description: This variable gives the operational status of the link. The value of initial is used when the link was administratively enabled but the configuration is incorrect, and the link cannot be activated.

mpoaAtmLinkName.name: mpoaAtmLinkName
mpoaAtmLinkName.description: A unique 31-character ascii string used to name the link.

mpoaAtmLinkDefaultVc.name: mpoaAtmLinkDefaultVc
mpoaAtmLinkDefaultVc.description: Index of the PVC to be used as the default channel for broadcast destination and unicast traffic. Not valid to set if the VSP is a non-replicating port.

mpoaAtmLinkFailOverLink.name: mpoaAtmLinkFailOverLink
mpoaAtmLinkFailOverLink.description: This variable contains the link id (link resource id) of the link to be used for fail over mode. This variable must not be set unless fail over mode is desired. The fail over link must have PVCs that are associated with another physical port, not the default port.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_0.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_0
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_0.description: This variable contains the PVC Resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 0. In total, there are 8 priority levels and 8 PVCs to be assigned. The same PVC can be specified for all levels.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_1.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_1
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_1.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 1.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_2.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_2
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_2.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 2.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_3.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_3
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_3.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 3.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_4.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_4
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_4.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 4.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_5.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_5
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_5.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 5.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_6.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_6
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_6.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 6.

mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_7.name: mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_7
mpoaAtmLinkOutPriority_7.description: This variable contains the PVC resource id (index) of the PVC assigned to outbound priority level 7.

mpoaAtmLinkRowStatus.name: mpoaAtmLinkRowStatus
mpoaAtmLinkRowStatus.description: This variable is included with every SET PDU to indicate whether the SET PDU contains a create or delete transaction type.

mpoaPvcTable.name: mpoaPvcTable
mpoaPvcTable.description: A table of all the PVCs created for MPOA traffic on the ATM module. The maximum number of expected entries is 128k.

mpoaPvcEntry.name: mpoaPvcEntry
mpoaPvcEntry.description: An entry containing management information pertaining to an MPOA PVC. This table has 3 indicies: vsp id, link id and resource id.

mpoaPvcVspIndex.name: mpoaPvcVspIndex
mpoaPvcVspIndex.description: Index of the VSP that this link and PVC is associated with.

mpoaPvcLinkIndex.name: mpoaPvcLinkIndex
mpoaPvcLinkIndex.description: The Link Id number of the link associated with this PVC.

mpoaPvcResIndex.name: mpoaPvcResIndex
mpoaPvcResIndex.description: The Resource Id associated with the PVC. It is associated with a port,vpi, and vci. Resource Ids are re-assigned each time the switch is re-booted. To get a valid resource id, application must first get value of mpoaNextPvcResourceId, before creating a new entry.

mpoaPvcPort.name: mpoaPvcPort
mpoaPvcPort.description: Physical port that this PVC is associated with. This variable is only modifiable at CREATE time.

mpoaPvcVpi.name: mpoaPvcVpi
mpoaPvcVpi.description: The PVC virtual path identifier(VPI). Must be unique among all VPIs configured for the ATM module. This variable is only modifiable at CREATE time.

mpoaPvcVci.name: mpoaPvcVci
mpoaPvcVci.description: The PVC virtual circuit identifier(VCI). Must be unique among all VCIs configured for the ATM module. This variable is only modifiable at CREATE time.

mpoaPvcInPriorityMap.name: mpoaPvcInPriorityMap
mpoaPvcInPriorityMap.description: The inbound priority map is the priority to be assigned to frames received on this PVC as they are passed on to the local VLAN segment.

mpoaPvcTrafficClass.name: mpoaPvcTrafficClass
mpoaPvcTrafficClass.description: The assigned service category for the PVC. This variable is only modifiable at CREATE time.

mpoaPvcPCR.name: mpoaPvcPCR
mpoaPvcPCR.description: Peak cell rate in cells per second.

mpoaPvcSCR.name: mpoaPvcSCR
mpoaPvcSCR.description: Sustainable cell rate in cells per second. Ignored for UBR and CBR.

mpoaPvcRowStatus.name: mpoaPvcRowStatus
mpoaPvcRowStatus.description: This variable must be included with every SET PDU to indicate whether the PDU contains a CREATE, DELETE, or MODIFY transaction type.

mpoaVspId.name: mpoaVspId
mpoaVspId.description: Used in the mpoaTrapLinkChange trap. Index of the VSP that the trap represents. If the link Id is non-zero than the vspId is the Id of the VSP associated with the link whose operational state has changed. If the link Id is zero, then the vspId represents the VSP whose operational state has changed.

mpoaLinkId.name: mpoaLinkId
mpoaLinkId.description: Used in the mpoaTrapLinkChange trap. Index of the link that the trap represents. If the link Id is non-zero than it is the Id of the link whose operational state has changed. If the link Id is zero, then it should be ignored.

mpoaOperState.name: mpoaOperState
mpoaOperState.description: This variable gives the operational status of the link or VSP. The value of initial is used when the link/VSP was administratively enabled but the configuration is incorrect, and the link/VSP cannot be activated.

mpoaTrapLinkChange.name: mpoaTrapLinkChange
mpoaTrapLinkChange.description: A mpoaTrapLinkChange trap is generated when a VSP or ATM link changes operational state.
